\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 T}{\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 he two representatives of Dark and Light had agreed to meet at the Halfway Tavern in Limbo, there to set in motion the Contest that had been agreed \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
between them.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Limbo was a gray sort of place with very even lighting. It existed between the Abode of Light and the Abode of Dark, a nebulous waiting-room sort of a place, vague at the best of times, but not entirely devoid of qualities.

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 There was the Half\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
way Tavern, for example, situated right in the middle of Limbo. The tavern was a queer, rickety old wooden building with a crazy tilted roof. It had been built on the line that separates the part of Limbo nearest Heaven from the part nearest Hell. This pl
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 a\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ce didn't get much business, but it was support-ed by equal contributions from Light and Dark. It was maintained for the succor of those spirits who happened to find themselves passing through on their way to somewhere else.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "So this is the famous Halfway \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Tavern!" said the Archangel Michael. "I've never been here before. Do they have a decent sort of a kitchen?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "It is reputed to be quite good," said Mephistopheles. "But half an hour later, you don't know that you've eaten anything. Persuasive but insubstan\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 tial, like the rest of Limbo."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "What's that region down there?" Michael asked, pointing.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mephistopheles peered. "Oh, that's the waiting area. In the old days, that's where they sent virtuous pagans and unbaptized babies, to wait until something could be do\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ne with them. That's not important nowadays, but a lot of people still find their way there for one reason or another."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I wonder if this is the best place for our meeting," Michael said, for he didn't like the look of some of the things he could see going\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  on in the waiting area.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
"It was agreed beforehand between your people and mine," Mephistopheles said. "Limbo is neutral territory, neither fish nor fowl, and certainly not good red meat. What better place for us to meet and begin the contest? Come, shall 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 we go in?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Michael nodded a little reluctantly, but proceeded into the tavern.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Michael was tall even for an archangel, and well made, since heavenly bodies tended toward athleticism. He had black kinky hair and a hooked nose and olive skin, souvenirs of hi\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
s Semitic and Persian ancestors. In the old days, Michael had been the guardian angel of Israel, back when there were still local deities who had not been subsumed into the One God system that had proven so popular on Earth. Michael could have had divine 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 c\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
osmetic surgery, since in Heaven you can look any way you want, as long as you don't use your looks for your personal advantage, but he kept his features in memory of the old time, even though he could have been a blue-eyed blond like the other archangels
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 .\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  He thought wiry black hair and aquiline features lent him an air of distinction.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "It's chilly out there," Mephistopheles said, rubbing his hands together briskly. He was of average height for a high officer in the ranks of Darkness, lean, with a long, nar\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
row face, long-fingered hands, and small, shapely feet that he kept in patent-leather pumps. His hair was jet black, sleeked straight back, with a natural part in the middle. He wore a small moustache and a pointed beard of the type known as an imperial b
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 e\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 cause he had been told it made him look untrustworthy.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "But how could it be cold?" Michael asked. "In Limbo there is neither hot nor cold."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "People say that," Mephistopheles said, "but it's not true. That stuff about Limbo having no qualities is patently f\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
alse. There's enough light to see by, isn't there? And if you can have light, why not cold?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "In Limbo," Michael said, somewhat pompously, "one sees by the inner vision."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "And shivers with the internal cold, I suppose," Mephistopheles said. "No, you're wro\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ng about this one, Michael. The wind that blows through Limbo can sometimes be exceedingly biting, blowing as it does from the direction of Despair."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I'm not wrong," Michael said. "But I suppose it's part of the scheme of things that you and I should disa\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
gree, representing, as we do, two glorious but opposed viewpoints. And that is how it should be, of course."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I think that's my line," Mephistopheles said cheerfully, sitting down in the booth opposite Michael and drawing off his gray silk gloves. "I suppo\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
se we can agree that we disagree on almost everything."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Especially on the matter of cities versus country."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Yes. Our last contest left that inconclusive, didn't it?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mephistopheles was referring to the recent .great Millennial contest in which the forces\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 of Dark and Light had contested for control of mankind's destiny for the next thousand years. That contest had centered on the conceit proposed by a young demon named Azzie, who had reenacted the Prince Charming legend, intending to bring it this time to
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
a dolorous conclusion, and to do so through no machinations of his own, but solely through the spirit of Failure expressing itself through Prince Charming's concocted body. Good had gone for the bet, although the contest appeared to be biased in favor of 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 D\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ark. But Good always enters such contests, assuming that the pull of Good is so great among mankind, a sentimental lot, that someone has to weigh the scales in favor of Evil for there to be anything of an agonal nature going on at all.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The Dark side, for i\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ts part, delighted in putting forth schemes of an involved nature, since the Dark side of things feels at home only in complications. Light, being simple, albeit in a doctrinaire way, was pleased to confront the dubious inventions of Dark, oftentimes losi
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 n\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 g because you can only weight a scale so far before it comes crashing down on one side, which is then considered preordained.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The proprietor of the tavern came over. He was an indistinct fellow, as are all who stay for any length of time in Limbo, and the \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
only definite things about him were the cast in one eye and his large and clumsy feet.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Yes, my lord," he said to Mephistopheles, louting low. "What can I bring you?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "An ichor daiquiri will do very nicely," Mephistopheles said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Yes, lord. And could I int\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 erest you in a slice of devil's food cake? Fresh today!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "All right. And what else have you got?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "The ham is very nice today. We have a place in Purgatory that devils it for us especially."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "No blood sausages?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "That's only on Thursdays."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Well, bring alo\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ng the deviled ham," Mephistopheles said. To Michael he remarked, "Can't let the side down, can we?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Certainly not. But isn't it time we got down to business?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I'm ready," Mephistopheles said. "Did you bring along an agenda?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "No need," Michael said. "It\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
's all in my head. It has fallen to our lot to decide upon the next Millennial contest. Hopefully, also, we will settle the question of the Goodness or Badness of cities this time around."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "How quickly time passes when you're immortal!" said Mephistopheles\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
. "Being a master of one-pointed concentration has something to do with it too, of course. Well then, let the cities rise like mushrooms."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Like flowers is an apter image," Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Which is the truer image remains to be seen," Mephistopheles said. "\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 So, trot out one of your urban saints and my merry crew of demons and I will have him foreswearing Good in no time."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "No, he needn't be a saint," Michael said, demonstrating again Good's irresistible tendency to give up advantages. "And anyhow, we have som\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ething more elaborate in mind. Something with a bit of sweep and grandeur to it to be held in a variety of times and places throughout the new millennium. But I'll tell you about that later. For now, are you acquainted with our servant Faust?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Of course,"\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 Mephistopheles said, though here he committed a typical error of the Dark side, pretending to knowledge that he didn't have. "You mean Johann Faust, of course, the well-known magician and mountebank who resides in\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 
