\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 M}{\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ack awoke with the feeling that there was someone in the tent with him. It had grown dark. He must\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 have slept for hours. Someone had provided a lighted candle in an earthenware bowl. Wasyl, no doubt. Its flickering flame threw wild shadows on the walls of the tent. They looked almost like a man; a fantastic man with black and gray garments, piercing e
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 y\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
es, floating hair; the kind of man you wouldn't want to meet at night. It was strange how close to the real thing was the apparition. Mack reached out and touched. The shadows gave under his fingers and felt for all the world like flesh and bone. Appalled
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ,\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  he shrank back.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "You poke me," the apparition said, "but you don't greet me. What kind of manners is that?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I didn't think you were real," Mack said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Nor am I, entirely. But then, neither are you. For you are not who you say you are."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "And your
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I say n\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ot who I am, hut you know who that is."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The apparition stepped into the light, revealing himself as one whose features Mack had reason to remember, since he had spied on his movements for several days before his accomplice, the Lett, had hit him over the h
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ead in the alley in Cracow.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "You are Dr. Faust!" Mack breathed.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "And you are a damned impostor!" Faust said in a grating voice.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 For just a fraction of a second Mack quailed before the fury of that accusation. Then he pulled himself together. Those who do w\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
rong have a code, too, just like those who do good, and like them they needs must strive to keep up their self-esteem, even their aplomb, in difficult times as well as good ones.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Now was an extremely difficult time: It was very embarrassing to be caught in\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 an impersonation, and worse to be face-to-face with the man he was pretending to be. It was the sort of situation that would cause a lesser man to pale and squeak, "Sorry, sir, I didn't know what I was doing, I'll give it up immediately, just please don'
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 t\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 have me hung." But Mack had not embarked on this role to give it up lightly. And so he strengthened his spirit, remembering that one who would play Faust on the stage of the world needs a little of the Faustian spirit if he's to get anywhere.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "We seem to \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 be at cross-purposes here," Mack said. "I doubt not that you are Faust. Yet I am Faust, too, on the authority of no less a person than Mephistopheles." .
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Mephistopheles was mistaken!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "When the great ones make mistakes, those mistakes become law."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Faust d\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
rew himself to his full height, which was rather shorter than Mack's, and said, "Must I listen to this casuistic palaver from one who speaks in my name? By the powers, I'll have vengeance if you don't vacate immediately and leave this game to the player f
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 o\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 r whom it was intended, namely, me."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "You think highly of yourself, that much is evident," Mack said. "But as to who was chosen, it seems to, be me. You can argue till kingdom come and you won't change that."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Argue? I'll do a lot more than argue! I'll bla\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 st you with spells of greatest puissance, and your punishment will be most hideously condign."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Will be what?" Mack asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Condign. It means fitting. I intend to give you a punishment worthy of your transgression."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "You know a lot of words honest folk nev\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
er use," Mack said hotly. "Now listen to this, Faust, I defy you utterly. And furthermore, I have the Powers of Darkness behind me all the way. The fact is, I make a better Faust than you!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Faust felt rage turn his eyeballs into reddened jelly, and he foug\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ht hard for control. He wasn't here to get into a shouting match. He wanted his rightful place in the Millennial contest. And it seemed that threatening Mack\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 against whom he could do nothing anyway\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 
was a waste of time.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I'm sorry I lost my temper," Faust s\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 aid. "Let's talk reasonably."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Another time, perhaps," Mack said, for just then the tent flap was drawn back and Wasyl entered. He looked suspiciously at Faust.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Who is this?" he asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "An old acquaintance," Mack said. "His name doesn't matter. He was jus\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 t leaving."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Wasyl turned to Faust, who noticed that the plump, clerkly young man had a naked dagger in his hand and a nasty expression on his face.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 \hich\f0 "Yes," Faust said, "I was just going. Till next time\'85\loch\f0 " He made himself say it. "Faust."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Yes, till next time\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ," Mack said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Wasyl asked, "Who's the woman outside the tent?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Oh, that's Marguerite," Faust said. "She's with me."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "See that you take her with you," Wasyl said. "We don't want any stray strumpets crumpling the wicket."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Faust held his tongue, for he dared\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  not reveal himself without first conferring with Mephistopheles. The great demon would not take it kindly if anyone aborted his contest.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Faust stepped outside and started walking. Marguerite, who had been waiting beside the tent flap, caught up with him a\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 nd said, "So what happened?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Nothing, yet," Faust said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "What do you mean, nothing? Didn't you tell him who you are?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Of course."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Then why don't you simply take over?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Faust stopped and looked at her. "It's not so simple. I need to talk to Mephistophele\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 s first, and I haven't found him yet."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 He turned to walk again, and found three soldiers in steel caps bearing pikes standing and looking at him.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Hey, you!" said one of the soldiers.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Me?" Faust said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "There's nobody else here except her, and I'm not talk\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ing to her."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Yes?" said Faust. "What do you want?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "What are you doing here?" the soldier asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "None of your business," Faust said. "What makes it your concern?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "We've been told to keep an eye open for fellows like you, skulking around the tents withou\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 t anything to do. You'd better come with us."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Faust saw that he had spoken without thinking. Hasty grandiloquence was a fault of the Faustian character that Mack didn't seem to share. He would have to watch that. For now, he would talk nicely.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Gentlemen, \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 I can explain everything."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Tell it to the captain of the guard," the soldier said. "Now come along quietly or we'll let you feel the end of a pike."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 And with that they led Faust and Marguerite away.
