\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 S}{\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 o what's new?" Mack asked, as soon as Faust\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  and Marguerite had departed.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Great news, lord," Wasyl said. "The doge Henry Dandolo himself wishes to see you immediately."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Ah, indeed?" Mack said. "Do you know what he wants?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "He didn't confide in me," Wasyl said. "But I have my suspicions."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Share th\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
em with me, good servant, while I wash my face and comb my hair." He proceeded to do those things, and to wish that Mephistopheles and the witches had remembered to supply him with a change of linen. "What is Henry Dandolo like?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "He is a fearsome old man,\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
" Wasyl said. "As doge of Venice, he is commander of one of the most powerful and well-disciplined fighting forces in all Christendom. We Crusaders are dependent on the Venetians for our transport and general stores, and they do not fail to remind us of i
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 t\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
. Dandolo himself is blind and somewhat frail of body, being now in his nineties. He's at an age when most noblemen would be content to lie at ease in their country estates and have servants bring them sweetened gruel. Not Henry Dandolo! He has ridden all
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
the way from Europe, and was seen in the battle lines at Szabo, where he demanded the Crusaders reduce that proud Hungarian city if they wished to secure Venice's cooperation in this Crusade. And so they did, but with much grumbling, because what began as
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 a holy enterprise has been perverted into just another Venetian commercial venture. Or so some people say. I myself have no opinion on the matter until I hear your own."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Wise of you," Mack said, running his fingers through his hair.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Your opportunities in\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  this meeting," Wasyl said, "are manifold."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "No doubt."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "An alliance of your interests with those of Venice could bring you wealth undreamed-of. And of course there is the other alternative."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "What's this?" asked Mack. For Wasyl had taken out his dagger, t\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ested its point on the ball of his thumb, and put the weapon down gently on the table.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "That, my lord, is an instrument of good Toledo steel that you might find useful if your interests are not aligned with those of Venice."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mack also tested the dagger's p\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
oint on the ball of his thumb, for that was the customary thing you did with weapons in those times. He slipped the weapon into his sleeve, commenting, "This may come in useful if I need to make a point." Wasyl smiled obligingly.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Wasyl had commandeered two\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 soldiers with torches. They went ahead and lit the way for Mack. Wasyl offered to go along, but Mack, realizing it was time he got down to business, declined the offer. It was prudent to work alone at this point, because he couldn't tell when Wasyl might
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 realize that his interests didn't coincide with Mack's at all.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 And so he started out. As he walked, he noticed that there was considerable commotion in the camp. Groups of soldiers were running here and there, and mailed horsemen rode past at a gallop. Man\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
y campfires were lit, and there was an atmosphere as of some great enterprise.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The doge's tent was a grand pavilion made of a white silken cloth through which lamplight gleamed. The doge himself was seated on a little chair before a table. There was a tray\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 before him, and on that tray was a quantity of precious gems, unset. Henry Dandolo was fingering them. He was a huge man, still imposing despite his great age. Now he seemed almost lost in his stiff, brocaded clothing. There was a small velvet cap on his
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
head with the hawk's feather of Venice set in it at a jaunty angle. His narrow face was unshaven, gray stubble catching silver glints from the firelight. He had a thin, sunken mouth tightly held, and his eye sockets showed the cloudy blue-gray of cataract
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 i\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 c sightlessness. He didn't look up as the servant announced the presence of Lord Faust, newly arrived from the west.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Come in, take a seat, my dear Faust," Henry Dandolo said, his voice booming and vibrant, speaking a correct but accented German. "The serv\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ants have set out the wine, have they not? Take a glass, my good sir, and make yourself at home in my humble quarters. Do you like these baubles?" He gestured at the tray of jewels.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I have seen their like from time to time," Mack said, bending over the tr\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ay. "But never finer. These have a brilliant luster and appear to be exceptional specimens."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The ruby is especially fine, is it not?" Dandolo asked, lifting a gem the size of a pigeon's egg in his thick white fingers and turning it this way and that. "It w\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
as sent me by the Nabob of Taprobane. And this emerald"\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 his fingers went to it unerringly\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 "hath a remarkable fire for its size, think you not?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Indeed I do," said Mack. "But I marvel, sir, that sightless as you are, you can yet perceive these qualities an\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 d make such distinctions. Or have you developed an eyesight in your fingertips?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Dandolo laughed, a harsh bass cackle ending in a dry cough. "Eyes in my fingertips! What a fancy! Yet betimes I believe it to be so, for my hands so love to touch fine gems th\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
at they have developed their own appreciation of them. Fine cloth, too, is a favorite of mine, as it is of any true Venetian, and I can tell you more about the tightness of warp and woof than a Flanders weaver. Yet these are but an old man's fancies. I ha
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 v\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 e something more valuable than that."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Indeed, sir?" Mack said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Take a look at this." The old man reached behind him and his fingers found and opened the lid of a large wooden chest. Reaching in, he took out the gorgeously painted wooden picture that had \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
nestled in the crushed velvet.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Do you know what this is?" Dandolo demanded.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Indeed I do not," Mack said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "It is the icon of the holy St. Basil. Its possession is said infallibly to ensure the continuing safety and prosperity of the city of Constantinople\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 . Do you know why I show you this?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I can't imagine, my lord."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Because I want you to take a message to your master. Are you listening carefully?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I am," Mack said, his mind filled with conjectures.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Tell the Holy Father in Rome that I spit on him and hi\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 s mean-minded excommunication. As long as this icon is in my possession, I have no need for his blessings."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "You want me to tell him that?" Mack asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Word for word."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "So I shall, if it is ever my fortune to meet the Holy Father."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Do not toy with me," D\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 andolo said. "Although you disguise it, I know you are his representative."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I most respectfully beg to differ," Mack said. "I don't come from the Pope. I represent different interests."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "You're really not from the Pope?'
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The old man's blind gaze was so fi\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 erce that even if Mack had been the Pope's emissary he would have denied it.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Absolutely not! Quite to the contrary!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The old man paused and took that in. "Quite to the contrary, eh?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Yes, exactly!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Who }{\cs17\i\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 are}{\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  you representing?" Dandolo demanded.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I'm sure \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 you can figure it out," Mack said, deciding to try some Faustian indirection.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Dandolo thought. "I've got it! You must be from Green Beard the Godless! He's the only one who doesn't have a representative here!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mack had no idea who Green Beard was, but he d\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ecided to play along.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I won't say yes and I won't say no," he said. "But if I }{\cs17\i\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 were}{\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 representing this Green Beard, what might you have to say to him?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Tell Green Beard that we welcome him to our venture, and we are aware of the unique role that only he ca\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 n play."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "He'll be interested to hear that. But what specifically?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "He must begin his attack on the Barbary Coast no later than one week from now. Can you get that message to him in time?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 There are many things I can do," Mack said. "But first I must know\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  why."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "The reasons should be evident. Unless Green Beard, who commands the pirates of the Peloponnesus, neutralizes them, the corsairs of the Barbary Coast are apt to put a crimp in our plans."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Yes, indeed," Mack said. "Which plans were those, by the way\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
"Our plans to take over Constantinople, of course. We Venetians have stretched our seapower to the utmost in getting this group of Franks hither to Asia. If a pirate attack should come on our Dalmatian dependencies while we are otherwise engaged, I fear
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  we should be hard-pressed."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mack nodded and smiled, but within he was boiling with excitement. So Dandolo was planning to capture Constantinople! By no stretch of the imagination could that be considered protecting it. It seemed clear that Dandolo had to 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 go, and never would the time be better than right now, while he was alone with the blind old man in his tent, at a time when the camp of the Franks was in a state of excitement. Mack slipped the knife out of his sleeve.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "You understand," Dandolo said, fond\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ling his ruby, "my plans for this fine city are far-reaching indeed, and no man but yourself and your pirate chief will know what I intend."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "It is a great honor," Mack said, trying to decide whether to insert the knife from front or back.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Constantinople \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
is a city that has seen better days," Dandolo said. "Once great and feared throughout the world, it is now an effete shadow of itself due to the ineffectual rule of its stupid kings. I'll bring that to a stop. No, I shall not reign myself. Command of Veni
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 c\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
e is enough for me! But I will put my own man on the Byzantine throne, and he will have orders to restore the city to its former majesty and greatness. With Venice and Constantinople allied, all the world will look with wonder at the age of great commerce
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 and learning that will ensue."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mack hesitated. He had been ready to strike. But Dandolo's words conjured up a vision of a great city restored to its full powers, a city in the forefront of learning and commerce, a place that could be a turning point in the
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  history of the world.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "And what religion would these Greeks follow?" Mack asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Despite my differences with the Pope," Dandolo said, "I am a good Christian. Young Alexius has made me promises of the most solemn sort, that once in power he will return hi\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
s subjects to the rightful See of Rome. Then the Pope will lift my excommunication, nay, may even see fit to canonize me, for so great a feat of conversion has not been heard of in modern times."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "My lord!" Mack cried. "Your vision is holy and enchanted in\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 deed! Count on me, my lord, to aid you in whatever way I can!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The old man reached out and caught Mack in a close embrace. Mack could feel the stiff bristles of the old man's face, and the warm salt of his tears as he raised his voice to praise Heaven. Mac\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
k was about to say a few words in favor of Heaven, too, because it could do no harm, when suddenly men-at-arms burst into the tent.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "My lord!" they cried. "The attack has begun! Villhardoin leads the soldiers even now to assault the walls!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Take me to the\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  action!" Dandolo cried. "I'll fight in this just cause myself! My armor, quick! Faust, give my offer to Green Beard, and we'll talk more later!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 And with that the old man swept out of the tent on the arms of his servitors, taking the holy icon with him, b\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ut leaving behind the bag of jewels.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mack stood in the tented room, with shadows dancing up and down its silken walls, and decided this was going to work out very nicely. He was going to save Constantinople and make a profit at it, just like Henry Dandolo 
