\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "At Your Majesty's service," Mack said, and, noting that Marco's face had changed from a scowl into a rictus of annoyance, decided that he had made no friends here this day.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "And what of the woman?" Kublai \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Khan asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mack hissed at Marguerite, "He's talking to you!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "What's he saying?" Marguerite said. "I can't understand a word!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I'll speak for you," Mack said. To Kublai Khan he said, "This is Marguerite, a friend of mine, but she doesn't have a word of M\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ongol."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "No word at all? But we would fain hear her story!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I'll just have to translate it for you," Mack said, "which is a shame because she tells it so well herself."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "That won't be necessary," Kublai said. "Luckily, we have recently instituted a rapid-\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 learning center for subjects and friends who don't understand Mongolian. You speak it perfectly, my dear Faust."

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Thank you," Mack said, bowing. "I've always had a bit of a knack for languages."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "But the woman is going to have to learn. Explain to her that\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  she is to go to class now and come out when she can speak to us."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mack said to Marguerite, "Look, I'm sorry about this, but they're taking you off to language class."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Oh, no," Marguerite said. "Not school again!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Yes. I'm sorry. There's nothing I can do\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  about it."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Darn it!" Marguerite said. "This is no fun at all!" But she let herself be led away by two serving maids.
