\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 T}{\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 he Main Banquet Room was filled with workm\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
en putting up paper streamers, banners, brightly colored tapestries, and other gewgaws of a festive nature. The ceiling was lofty and was held up by eight pillars. Each of those pillars rested on a square block that gave some room at its corners for decor
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 a\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
tions. The main decoration for the festivities was severed human heads. Marco had heads piled on these corner stones, great piles of severed heads, some of them still bleeding, some rather dried out, some in a state of mummification, others in a state of 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 m\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
oldiness, decay, or even putrescence. In the middle of the room was a vat of blood, with two cowled figures stirring it so it wouldn't coagulate. Marco was standing near to it, hands on his hips, supervising the placement of the heads.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mack paused a moment\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  to take it in, then walked up to Marco. "Nice-looking arrangement of heads," he commented.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Thank you," Marco said. "But they're still not right."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 He shouted to the men on ladders piling the heads, "Tighten up that pyramid! I don't want those heads scatte\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
red around. I'm after a concentrated effect. I want them piled high! A pyramid of heads about seven feet high, that's what I'm after on each of the corner stones. I know they won't balance by themselves. You'll have to devise some way to get them to look 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 l\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ike they're balancing. Find some bracing material, or use twine or haywire, but make sure it doesn't show. And take those dried-out old heads out of the pile. They look like they've been lying around for decades. This isn't a tribute to the past. We're ce
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 l\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ebrating the Khan's present and future conquests and all we want here are freshly severed heads, preferably with the blood still dripping. If the blood isn't fresh, add some from the vat."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mack and Marco watched for a while. The workmen made adjustments. M\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ack commented, "The display looks much better now."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Do you think so?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Oh, yes. You Venetians have an eye for these matters."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Thank you. So you're from Ophir?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Yes," Mack admitted. "But let's not talk about me. I just wanted to tell you how nice it is t\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
o meet you. I admire you, Marco. It's an honor to meet the foremost fabulist of your generation, perhaps of any generation."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "That's good of you," Marco said. "But you're a fabulist, too, aren't you? I mean, Ophir, what's that if not fabulistic?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Oh, only\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  in a very minor way. After all, who cares about Ophir? After you've mentioned the ivory, peacocks, and apes, there really isn't much to say about the place."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Marco smiled a thin, dangerous smile. "I hope not. There's only room for one fabulist at a time i\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 n a royal court."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Hey, you're the resident fabulist," Mack said. "As a matter of fact, you're the reason I came here. I want to get your autograph."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "You have my book?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "It's my dearest possession. Was, I should say, for thieving Arabs stole my copy from \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 me one night in High Tartary."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "That sounds like quite a tale."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Not at all," Mack said, remembering who was supposed to be the storyteller around here. "Actually, it was the most banal burglary imaginable. But it was bad luck for me because I don't have a\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 copy for you to sign. But if you could put your signature on a piece of paper, I'd paste it in when I get a copy again."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I just might happen to have a copy," Marco said carelessly. "I suppose I could let you have it at cost."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Your only copy? I couldn't!\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "As a matter of fact, I have several."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I'd consider it a privilege if you'd sign a copy for me. And I'd consider it a privilege if you'd let me guard your person and keep you safe from the plots and cabals that swirl around your glorious person."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "How d\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 id you know about the plots against me?" Marco asked. "You just got here."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "It is common knowledge," said Mack, "that a man as talented and famous as you must have enemies. It would be my desire to protect you from them."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "If you really want to help," Marc\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 o said, "there is something you could do for me."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Just tell me," Mack said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Marco said, "As ambassador of Ophir, I take it you speak quite a few languages."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "It's a prerequisite of being an ambassador," Mack said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I already know that you speak German, Fr\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ench, Mongol, and Persian."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "They're necessary, of course."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "And what about Turkestani? Farsi? Turkoman? What about Oglut and Mandarin?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I can get by in them," Mack said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "What about Pushtu?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I'm not sure," Mack said. "What does it sound like?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Marco hel\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 d his mouth in a special way and said, " 'This is how a sentence in Pushtu sounds.'"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Yes," Mack said, "I can understand that."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Perfect," Marco said. "The Princess Irene speaks only Pushtu, having never mastered the Mongol tongue. She has no one to talk t\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 o."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Except for yourself, surely?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "The only sentence I have learned thus far is, 'This is how a sentence in Pushtu sounds.' I've had no time to study it, you see."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "That's too bad."
