 shuffled over, and, laughing his uncanny laugh, said, "Yes, Faust, it was agreed upon, but only on condition that you give me a Traveling Spell that will provide the motive power to take us there. The ship of the dead doesn't run through space and time o
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 n\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  oars alone, you know."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Faust turned to Azzie. "About that Traveling
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Spell. My own is considerably depleted. Do you think you could spare me a spell recharge? Or better yet, give me a whole new Traveling Spell and Charon and I will be on our way."
