nning, their footsteps echoing on the cobblestones. There was an air of holiday glee. Many drunks had gotten an early start and were sleeping it off in doorways. Children were everywhere, darting here and there in an ecstasy of pleasure. The shops were al
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 l\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 closed, with boards nailed up over their doorways. A clatter of hooves was heard as mounted lancers rode by, brilliant in uniforms of scarlet and black, and Mack ducked back into a doorway to avoid getting trampled on. As he did so, he ran into a man's s
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 o\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 lid body. "Watch where you're going!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Sorry!" said Mack. "It was the soldiers."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "What did soldiers have to do with you stepping on my foot?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The man whose foot Mack had stepped on in the doorway was tall and finely shaped, with a head that could have mode\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
led for a Grecian Apollo. He was fashionably dressed in a cloak of dark fur, and from his hat floated an ostrich feather, proof that he either had contacts abroad or knew someone in the Florence Zoo. He peered intently at Mack with large and brilliant eye
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 s\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 .
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Excuse me, stranger," the man said, "but haven't we met?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I doubt it," Mack said. "I'm not from around here."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "That's interesting. I'm looking for a man who doesn't come from around here. My name is Pico della Mirandola. Perhaps you've heard of me?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 In\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 deed Mack had, from Mephistopheles, as one of the great alchemists of the Renaissance. But Mack, foreseeing trouble, was not going to admit having heard of him.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I don't think so," Mack said. "Anyhow, it's just a coincidence us meeting this way. It's very \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 unlikely that I'd be the man you seek."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "So it might seem in the ordinary course of things," Pico said. "But when you put magic to work, coincidences suddenly become much more probable. I was supposed to meet someone here. Might it not be you?"
