ust, must have used his magical powers to contact this fellow. Pico della Mirandola was or had been a magician of great and sinister reputation. He and Faust had probably been corresponding across the centuries. It was said that magicians could do that, s
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 i\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 nce even death was no impediment to real magic.
