that no one was looking at him, and pulled the painting out before the flames had reached it. It looked as good as new. He put it to one side and looked around for others. There was a Giotto, but the surface had already begun bubbling in the heat. He soug
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 h\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
t hungrily after others. If saving one Botticelli was good, saving two ought to be excellent. And lucrative as well! And surely it was not wrong to serve Art! Especially when it was just lying around waiting to be burned! Those other choices Mephistophele
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 s\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  had given him had just sounded too weird. He was sure no one could object to a man who rescued great art.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Then there was a hand on his shoulder. A thin, splendidly dressed man with a short beard was staring at him severely.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Sir, what are you doing?"
