\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Where are we now?" Mack asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "This is a tavern in the \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
Latin Quarter of Paris," Mephistopheles said. "I feel at home with students. They have always had a lively regard for the devil. And Paris, of course, is the devil's own city. I thought it would be an appropriate place to begin the last act in our contest
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 .\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
Mack looked around. He and Mephistopheles were seated at a long rough-hewn wooden table. There were others at the table, all young men, students by the look of them. They were immersed in their own conversations, which were carried on in loud voices and 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
with elaborate gestures and much shrugging. The tavern was dark, extensive, and low-ceilinged. Waiters hurried back and forth carrying trays crowded with tumblers of wine, with plates of mussels in a red sauce, and with wedges of bread on the side. There 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 w\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ere loud guffaws of laughter, catcalls, bursts of song. These students were young and had the whole world ahead of them, and they were studying in Paris, already the most notable city in Europe and therefore in the world.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "What's happening this time?" Mack\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
"This is the year 1789," Mephistopheles said. "Paris, indeed, all France, is in an uproar. Spurred on by the recent American Revolution, the common people are ready to rise and throw out the ineffective royal court and the corrupt nobles. It is the
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 dawn of a new age for the masses, and sunset for the privileged few. In the palace of the Tuileries, the desperate Louis the Sixteenth and his wife, Marie Antoinette, frightened by the threats and insults heaped on them by an increasingly unmanageable po
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 p\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ulace, are preparing to flee this very night, taking a coach to Belgium, where they will meet up with royalist armies burning to avenge the insult to the royal family."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Sounds exciting," Mack said. "Do they make it?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Alas, it is not to be. History tells \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
us that at crucial moments, things go wrong. At the end, the royal family is brought back to Paris by the Republican Guard. Soon after, they will lose their heads to the guillotine."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Are they very evil, this king and queen?" Mack asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mephistopheles smi\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
led sadly. "Not evil at all. Merely creatures of their time and place. Their deaths will solve nothing, and the act of destroying them will revolt the world. There will be battles and massacres, and France will stand alone with the armies of Europe agains
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 t\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  her."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I suppose you want me to save the king and queen."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "What you do is entirely up to you, of course," Mephistopheles said. "But it }{\cs17\i\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 would}{\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  be a notable deed."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "What should I do?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "The escape is set for tonight. One by one, the royal family will come out\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
 of the palace and get into coaches driven by loyalists. But right at the beginning there will be a fatal delay. Marie Antoinette will take so long at her preparations that the escape will be set back some hours. Because of this delay, the duc de Choiseul
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ,\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  waiting in a wood outside Paris with a force of hussars loyal to the king, will conclude the escape is off and abandon his post. It is a key point."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "There are other key points?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Several others," Mephistopheles said. "Once the flight is underway, a certa\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
in Drouet will recognize the king as his coach passes through the village of Saint-Menehould. Drouet gives the alarm that leads to His Majesty's capture. His seeing the king is a matter of pure luck. If Drouet could be diverted\'85\loch\f0 "
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I'm beginning to get the \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 idea," Mack said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
"Or, failing that, the king and queen might still be saved if the bridge at Varennes were open rather than blocked. The blocked bridge prevents the royal coach from crossing to the Belgian frontier and safety. So there are three chances; 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Marie Antoinette's delay, Drouet's recognition, and the blocked bridge at Varennes. Change any of these and you change history. Are. you ready, Faust?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I think so," Mack said. "As ready as I'll ever be."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Excellent. And please, Johann, try to make this a \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
good one. It is the last, you know. I'll look in on you from time to time and see how you're getting on. Maybe even lend a hand." He winked. 'Till later!" And with that, Mephistopheles vanished.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 By asking a passing fishwife, Mack learned that Marie Antoine\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
tte was at Versailles, some leagues outside of Paris. In the Place Saint-Michel he found a public coach and paid a centime for a place on it. The streetcar, as it was called, drawn by four horses, clanged through Paris, stopping here and there to take on 
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 a\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 nd discharge passengers, until it passed beyond the city limits into a country lane that meandered through green fields and tasteful clumps of trees.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mack got off at the palace of Versailles and walked up to the main entrance. The armed guard at the door, \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
resplendent in the crimson and white of the queen's livery, raised his pike to the ready. "You, there! What do you want?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I crave an audience with the queen," Mack said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "She's not seeing anyone today," the guard said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Yes, I know. But this is urgent."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 I told you, she's not seeing anyone."
