hat kept track of facts about Earth for the Spiritual Kingdom. The computer was an innovation that many spirits both Good and Bad had fought against, for computers were considered newfangled inventions that time had not yet softened into acceptable custom
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 .\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  But many considered this a frivolous view. The consensus among the creatures of Dark and Light was that the appropriate rule here was, as }{\cs17\i\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
below, so above}{\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 , and that even the spirits had to keep up with the changing times on Earth.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Ylith went to an open ter\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 minal on the computer and introduced herself.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 The computer said, "I assume you have a problem. Tell me what I need to know."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Ylith wasted no time. "I need to find the correct hour of departure in an important historical situation. Marie Antoinette thinks t\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
he time to leave to meet the coachman who is going to take her out of Paris and away from the guillotine is eleven P.M. I have been told it is eight P.M. Which is correct?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I'm sorry," the computer said, after no more than a nanosecond's hesitation. "That\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 's classified information."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "It's a simple fact and it's got to be on record! It can't be classified!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "It's not, really," the computer said. "I was told to say it was if anyone asked for a fact of a certain class of facts."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "What class is that?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "The clas\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 s of simple and apparently easily ascertainable facts, which are, in fact, almost impossible to pin down."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Well, what's so difficult about looking it up for me or whatever it is you do?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "The fact itself is not the problem," the computer said. "It's the r\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 outine for looking up facts that's disabled just now."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Why?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Because the technicians are introducing a new packing order for the facts already on file. To be able to use it, they'll have to invent a new locating order that can make sense out of the new p\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
acking order."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "And meanwhile no one can find out anything? That's ridiculous! Why don't you do something about it?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Me?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Yes, you!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I'm not supposed to," the computer said. "They told me they'd let me know when they had it worked out."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "So you're sayin\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 g you don't know the fact I'm asking about?" Ylith said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I'm not saying that at all!" The computer's tone was hurt. "I know all the facts. It's just that my retrieval system is disabled. That makes it technically impossible for me to tell you."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Technical\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ly! But not virtually!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "No, of course not virtually."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "So give me a virtual answer. Or can't you even do that?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I could if I wanted to. But I don't want to."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Ylith heard hurt pride in the computer's voice. She decided to take a different tack. "Wouldn't \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 you do it for me?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Sure, babe. Just a moment." Lights flashed. Then the computer said, "I make it three A.M."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Impossible," Ylith said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Not what you expected? I told you, the retrieval system is down."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I know, hut you said you could bypass it."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I did. \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 It came up three A.M.!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Is that really the best you can do? All right, I'll have to make do with that. Thank you."
