\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 M}{\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ack was having a bit of a doze at the Hotel d\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 e Ville when someone shook him roughly by the shoulder.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "What is it?" He awoke with a start and peered into a small, bearded face.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I'm Rognir, the dwarf."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Oh, yes." Mack sat up and rubbed his eyes. "I guess you are. What can I do for you?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Nothing at al\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
l. But I bring news. Ylith asked me to come by and tell you she wasn't successful in hurrying up the queen. Something about uncertainty as applied to time, but I can't remember that part."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Damn!" Mack said. "So the royal carriage has left late on its ill-\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 fated run to Varennes!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "If you say so," Rognir said. "No one bothered to fill }{\cs17\i\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 me}{\insrsid13440386 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  in on what's going on."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mack said, "I'm trying to prevent the royal family from capture. But I don't know what to do now unless I can get a horse."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "A horse? What do you need\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  a horse for?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "So I can get to Saint-Menehould where I'll get my next chance to change the fate of Louis the Sixteenth and Marie Antoinette."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Why don't you get there by magic?" Rognir said, pouring out a mugful of wine for Mack.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I don't know the right w\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ords," Mack confessed.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "That other fellow would."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "What other fellow?'
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "The one I helped on the Styx."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "You mean Faust?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "That's who they tell me he was."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "I'm also Faust."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "If you say so."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "But he's trying to get rid of me!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Tough on you, then," Rognir s\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
aid. "Nothing personal. I figured that helping him would put out of joint the nose of a certain demon of my acquaintance. He shortchanged me on a recent work contract. Dwarves have long memories."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "And short, bristly beards," Mack said. "Damn! How am I to \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 get to Saint-Menehould before the royal carriage?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "You need to get out there and get a horse," Rognir said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mack stared at him. "You think it's as simple as that?'
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "It'd better be," Rognir said, "or you're really in a lot of trouble."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mack nodded. "You're\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  right. All right, I'm going."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Some time later, Mack was galloping through a dark forest upon a spirited black charger. He had seized it from a groom Rognir had located for him in front of the Tuileries, in the name of the Committee for Public Safety. No o
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ne had wanted to argue with him.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 And so he galloped along the dimly lit forest path congratulating himself on the fine mount he had chosen. Then he heard something behind him, turned and looked, then turned back and hunched over the horse's neck. Yes, he h
\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 ad a fast horse, but it wasn't fast enough to keep the rider behind him from gaining steadily.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 There was nothing he could do about it. The pursuer drew up even with him, and he saw it was Faust, the black tails of his long coat flapping wildly, stovepipe h\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
at pasted flat against his forehead by the wind, grinning maliciously.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "So, impostor, we meet again!" Faust cried.
