\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "That's Mack the Club!" Michael sai\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 d.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mephistopheles looked. "Are you quite sure? That is the man I've been dealing with during this contest."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Oh, it's definitely Mack," Michael said. "Is it possible that you made a mistake in Cracow, my dear demon? Has the wrong Faust been performing in y\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 our contest?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mephistopheles looked again, and his lips thinned. His dark eyes seemed to smolder. Glaring at Michael, he said, "I seem to see a fine spiritual hand in all this!"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "You give me too much credit," Michael said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Mephistopheles looked again. "Tha\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 t's definitely the fellow who's been doing the contest. Are you sure he's not Faust?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "Afraid not. His name is Mack, and he is a common criminal. I'm afraid you picked the wrong man to decide human destiny, my dear Mephistopheles."
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 "And you have picked the\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0  wrong devil if you think you can get away with this?"
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 Michael smiled but did not reply.
